-- Axtel, Capex, Cyrela and Petrobras: Latin America Equity Preview
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2010-10-13T07:31:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/axtel-capex-cyrela-and-petrobras-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The  MSCI Latin America Index  fell 0.3 percent to 4,523.62.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock. Brazil’s markets were closed yesterday for a bank holiday.  Argentina  Capex SA  (CAPX AF): The power generator is negotiating a
$13.5 million loan with Deutsche Bank AG to fund its Hychico
wind farm project, according to a filing posted on the website
of the securities regulator. Capex rose 3.3 percent to 3.15
pesos.  Brazil  Cyrela Brazil Realty SA  (CYRE3 BS): The real estate
developer announced after the market closed Oct. 11 it sold 300
million reais ($180 million) in four-year debentures among
institutional investors, according to a filing sent to
regulators. Cyrela rose 1.3 percent to 24.93 reais on Oct. 11.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar  (PCAR5
BS): The retailer said third-quarter net sales rose 17 percent
to 7.1 billion reais. The shares gained 1.3 percent to 61.80
reais on Oct. 11.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS): The state-controlled oil
company is set to launch a $224 billion investment program over
next 4 years and will hire between 12 and 15 additional
deepwater rigs in 2011, Robin Shoemaker, an analyst at Citigroup
Inc. said, citing sources close to the company. Petrobras fell
0.6 percent to 25.85 reais on Oct. 11.  Mexico  Axtel SAB de CV  (AZTELCPO MM): Mexico’s second-largest
land-line phone carrier began offering Internet download speeds
of up to 100 megabits a second to home and business users in
Mexico’s three largest cities, the company said in an emailed
statement. Axtel fell 0.3 percent to 7.5 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
